<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It's territory only the bravest fashionistas dare tread, but Jenni Falconer took the divisive double denim look one step further by wearing a blue jean jumpsuit on Tuesday. </p>

<p>The Scottish presenter, 44, caught the eye for all the right reasons as she left Global Radio Studios in the fitted one-piece and made her way across London's Leicester Square. </p>

<p>The near-skintight outfit served to accentuate fitness mad Jenni's slender physique following her latest stint on the airwaves.</p>

<p>Looking good: Jenni Falconer took the divisive double denim look on step further by wearing a blue jean jumpsuit on Tuesday</p>

<p>The Smooth Radio presenter added to her look with a large blue leather handbag, while battered white running shoes gave the overall ensemble a causal flourish. </p>

<p>Inevitably turning plenty of heads, Jenni gave onlookers a characteristically beaming smile as she made her way home.   </p>

<p>Away from radio it was recently announced that the health conscious star is the face and voice of newly launched fitness app Start 2 Run.</p>

<p>Stylish: The Scottish presenter, 44, caught the eye for all the right reasons as she left Global Radio Studios in the fitted one-piece and made her way across London's Leicester Square</p>

<p>Toned and trim: The near-skintight outfit served to accentuate fitness mad Jenni's slender physique following her latest stint on the airwaves</p>

<p>Finishing touches: The Smooth Radio presenter added to her look with a large blue leather handbag, while battered white running shoes gave the overall ensemble a causal flourish</p>

<p>The app is ideal for people who need help getting started running as well as people who want to up their running mileage or aim for a particular running distance goal.</p>

<p>Users will have Jenni with them for all their training sessions, encouraging and motivating, as well as providing tips and pointers.</p>

<p>She said of the new role: 'Start 2 Run is perfect for complete beginners and people who have started running during lockdown and hit the 5K distance.</p>

<p>Don't mind me: Jenni turned plenty of heads as she made her way home on Tuesday morning </p>

<p>'Running has become a lifeline for so many of us – as our daily exercise and a way of getting some fresh air.</p>

<p>'For many people, building up to a 5K or just beginning to jog short distances has shown the joy of running and this app is the perfect coaching tool to keep you going.'</p>

<p>The presenter is no stranger to keeping active and often shares images and videos of herself working out and staying fit on social media.</p>
